item.title: What does the curved arrow road marking mean?
item.description: ROAD markings in the UK are there to inform motorists. So, if you spot the curved arrow marking on the road, here is what it means. What does the curved arrow road marking mean? This arrow tells drivers who are attempting to overtake that they need to return to the left hand side of the road. These arrows are marked shortly before solid white lines. Where there are double lines in the middle of the road, rule 129 of the Highway Code states that drivers must not cross or straddle this.

item.title: What is cryotherapy and what are the benefits of the -200 degree chamber used by Katie Price and Gar
item.description: CRYOTHERAPY is a medical technique which uses cold temperatures for health benefits. It is sometimes referred to as cryosurgery, cryozone, cryoablation or cryosauna and uses a cryo-chamber. What is cryotherapy? Cryotherapy involves the application of sub-zero temperatures to treat diseased or dead tissue. For tailored treatments, it can be applied via a spray gun or cotton swabs to certain parts of the body. A whole-body treatment involves getting into a body-sized capsule – up to your neck – while liquid nitrogen is pumped into the air, cooling the entire chamber to -200°C.
